{"title": "Authentication", "source": "netexec", "source_label": "NetExec Wiki", "path": "vnc-protocol/authentication", "html": "<h1 id=\"authentication\">Authentication</h1>\n<h3 id=\"vnc-authentication\">VNC Authentication</h3>\n<h4 id=\"testing-credentials\">Testing credentials</h4>\n<p>Some VNC servers do not require a username. In such cases, the username field should be left empty, as illustrated in the results below.\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>nxc<span class=\"w\"> </span>vnc<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;ip&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-u<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s1\">&#39;&#39;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-p<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s1\">&#39;password&#39;</span>\n</code></pre></div></p>\n<p>Expected Results:\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">nxc vnc &lt;ip&gt; -u '' -p 'password'</code></pre>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>nxc<span class=\"w\"> </span>vnc<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;ip&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>-u<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s1\">&#39;&#39;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-p<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s1\">&#39;password&#39;</span>\nVNC<span class=\"w\">         </span>&lt;ip&gt;<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"m\">5900</span><span class=\"w\">   </span>&lt;ip&gt;<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">[</span>*<span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>RFB<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">3</span>.8\nVNC<span class=\"w\">         </span>&lt;ip&gt;<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"m\">5900</span><span class=\"w\">   </span>&lt;ip&gt;<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">[</span>+<span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>password<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span>Pwn3d!<span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div></p>\n<h4 id=\"specify-port\">Specify port</h4>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>nxc<span class=\"w\"> </span>vnc<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;ip&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>--port<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;port&gt;\n</code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"unauthenticated-access\">Unauthenticated access</h4>\n<p>When the VNC server doesn't require authentication, the following output can be expected.\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">nxc vnc &lt;ip&gt;</code></pre>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>nxc<span class=\"w\"> </span>vnc<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;ip&gt;\nVNC<span class=\"w\">         </span>&lt;ip&gt;<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"m\">5900</span><span class=\"w\">   </span>&lt;ip&gt;<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">[</span>*<span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>RFB<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">3</span>.8<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span>No<span class=\"w\"> </span>Auth:True<span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div></p>\n<h4 id=\"vnc-sleep\">VNC sleep</h4>\n<p>Increase the VNC socket connection sleep interval to prevent rate limiting.\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><code>nxc<span class=\"w\"> </span>vnc<span class=\"w\"> </span>&lt;ip&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>--vnc-sleep<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">5</span>\n</code></pre></div></p>", "excerpt": "Authentication VNC Authentication Testing credentials Some VNC servers do not require a username. In such cases, the username field should be left empty, as illustrated in the results below. nxc vnc &", "tags": []}